CAPE TOWN - Eight people sustained injuries varying from moderate to serious after two vehicles collided with a jumping castle in Eindhowen street in Delft on Wednesday afternoon. When ER24 arrived on scene at 16H08, another medical service was already on the scene as well as the fire department and the SAPS. Of the eight injured, six were children believed to be between the ages of three and seven. Two of the injured were adults. ER24 as well as another medical service on scene transported the patients to nearby hospitals for further medical care. The exact circumstances surrounding the incident are not yet known to the paramedics but local authorities were on scene for further investigations. CAPE ARGUS ADAPTED FROM PRESS RELEASE